York Region [southern Ontario] Public Health is alerting residents who may have visited 2 Markham [southern Ontario] locations in early May [2019] that they may have been exposed to the measles.

A Niagara region [southern Ontario] resident, whose travel-related case of measles is being investigated by Niagara Public Health, visited the following 2 locations in Markham [see source URL for specific locations]

For more information, visit http://www.york.ca/health

[Byline: Aileen Zangouei]

